I am a lecturer at the Alpen-Adria0Unviersity Klagenfurt Austria.

I was a senior research associate at the Unviersity of Bristol, UK in the cryptography research group from 2017 to 2019. Prior to that
I was postdoc researcher at the Technical University of Denmark in the cyber-security group.

I received PhD in Computer Science from the University of Luxembourg in 2014. My doctoral thesis supervisor was Prof. Alex Biryukov.

My __research interests__ lie in the area of cryptography and its applications. I am interested in design of cryptographic primitives,
cryptanalysis, quantum algorithms for cryptanalysis, and application of cryptography in security and privacy. I am also interested in statistical
machine learning and its interplay with cryptography and security.

<h5> PC member </h5>
I served as the PC member of Indocrypt 2020, PKC 2020, FSE 2019.
